headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum started slow and finished strong with 34 points, 11 rebounds and six assists, leading the Boston Celtics to a 111-99 victory over the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 34, Celtics cruise past Pistons 111-99

headlines.description: — Darius Garland and Jarrett Allen scored 23 points apiece and Donovan Mitchell added 21 to lead the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 114-91 rout of the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Allen each score 23, Cavaliers rout Wizards 114-91

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 29 points, Kawhi Leonard added 24 and the Los Angeles Clippers overcame a career-high 47 points from Cam Thomas in his first start to beat the short-handed Brooklyn Nets 124-116 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers surge late, overcome Thomas' 47 to top Nets 124-116

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic could be playing for another team by the end of the week. The same goes for Andre Drummond as the NBA's trade deadline approaches.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic, Drummond come up big, Bulls beat Spurs 128-104

headlines.description: — Keegan Murray had a career-high 30 points and set a franchise rookie record with eight 3-pointers to help the Sacramento Kings snap a two-game skid with a 140-120 win over the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray hits eight 3-pointers as Kings beat Rockets 140-120

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving hadn’t arrived yet and Luka Doncic was out, so it was time for the Dallas youngsters to shine.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green, Hardy help Mavs surprise Jazz 124-111 without Doncic

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — With star teammate Stephen Curry sidelined, Klay Thompson kept shooting and took care of the offensive load the Golden State Warriors were missing without their reigning NBA Finals MVP.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 42 points with 12 3s, Warriors beat Thunder

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez scored 27 points and the Milwaukee Bucks stretched their winning streak to eight games with a 127-108 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Trail Blazers 127-108 for 8th straight win
